subSubSection.paragraph:
Description
. 
Male
(
Holotype
). Total length 0.85. Carapace length 0.35, ovoid; narrowing gradually anteriorly, yellow with border black striated, flat pars cephalic, fovea absent (
Fig. 1A
). Clypeus length 0.02, with a pair of long bristles (
Fig. 2A
). Eyes with black border; PME oval; ALE and PLE rounded, ranging from opalescent or white (
Fig. 2A
). Chelicerae light yellow, promargin with seven teeth, attached to a very long lamina, retromargin with two small teeth (
Fig. 2C
). Sternum yellow. Endites yellow, with large serrula with more than 15 denticles, distal macrosetae paired and crosier-like, many multifid macrosetae present (
Fig. 2B
, arrow). Labium yellow, sulcated distally (
Fig. 2B
). Legs gray; formula 4123; total length: I 1.4; II 1.2; III 1.0; IV 1.7. Male palp: palpal femur length 0.02; palpal tibia enlarged basally, with four dorsal trichobothria (
Fig. 3B
); cymbium conical distally, bearing subdistal pair of modified setae and a projected and bifid tarsal organ (
Figs 2F
; 
3A
); bulb spherical (

Figs 1B 
–
D

; 

3C 
–
D

); conductor shorter than SCI (

Figs 1E 
–
F

; 

3E 
–
F

; 

4A 
–
B

); embolus with truncated SCII, conical SCIII and large and with three short projections in the SCIV (

Figs 1E 
–
F

; 

3E 
–
F

). Abdomen length 0.45, oval; uniformly grayish (
Fig. 1A
). Two epiandrous spigots, with large, conic and striated base (
Fig. 2D
). Colulus triangular with six bristles (
Fig. 2E
).

Female ( Paratype , IBSP 188899). Coloration as in male, except for darker carapace on the edges and orange chelicerae, and gray abdomen on the posterior edge (
Fig. 5A – C
). Total length: 0.81; carapace length: 0.4; Carapace as in male, light yellow pattern ( Fig. 5A ). Pedipalp without claw, with conical tip ( Fig. 6A ) and subdistal bifid tarsal organ. Clypeus: 0.02 diameter, with setae as in male. Eyes, chelicerae, sternum, endites and labium (
Fig. 4C – D
) as in male. Legs as in male; formula 4123, total length: I 1.4; II 1.2; III 1.0; IV 1.7. Abdomen length 0.42. Colulus triangular with six bristles ( Fig. 6B ). Genitalia externally with long and curved lateral plates, large ventral plate and terminal depression inconspicuous (
Figs 5B – D
;
6C – D
); internally with paired and contiguous spermathecae, and afferent spermathecae with distal narrow area ( Fig. 5E–F ).
